    <Statements>
      <Statement>Understand a multiple of a/b as a multiple of 1/b, and use this understanding to multiply a fraction by a whole number. &lt;i&gt;For example, use a visual fraction model to express 3 &amp;times; (2/5) as 6 &amp;times; (1/5), recognizing this product as 6/5. (In general, n &amp;times; (a/b) = (n &amp;times; a)/b.)&lt;/i&gt;</Statement>
